The comment mentions "[databind#731]" which refers to skipping serializer lookup if the type is nominally `java.lang.Object`. However, the current code unconditionally calls `provider.findValueSerializer(delegateType)` even when `delegateType` is `java.lang.Object`, which can cause issues.

Looking at similar patterns in `createSerializer` (lines 35-39) and `findConvertingSerializer` (lines 56-58), they both have checks for `java.lang.Object` before calling serializer lookup, but `createContextual` is missing this check.

The fix is to add a conditional check to skip the serializer lookup when `delegateType` is `java.lang.Object`:

