Looking at this code, I need to identify the bug(s). Let me analyze each function carefully.

After reviewing the code, I found the issue in the `_createAndCacheUntypedSerializer(JavaType type)` method. The function declares that it returns `JsonSerializer<Object>`, but when `ser` is null (after the exception handling), the method doesn't return anything and will fall through to the end without a return statement.

Comparing with the similar function `_createAndCacheUntypedSerializer(Class<?> rawType)`, which has proper return handling, I can see the issue clearly.

Here's the bug:
```java
protected JsonSerializer<Object> _createAndCacheUntypedSerializer(JavaType type)
    throws JsonMappingException
{        
    JsonSerializer<Object> ser;
    try {
        ser = _createUntypedSerializer(type);
    } catch (IllegalArgumentException iae) {
        ser = null;
        reportMappingProblem(iae, iae.getMessage());
    }

    if (ser != null) {
        _serializerCache.addAndResolveNonTypedSerializer(type, ser, this);
    }
    return ser;  // <-- This is missing!
}
```

The fix is to add a `return ser;` statement at the end of the method.

